Date: Sun, 25 Feb 2001 07:17:06 +0530
From: Santanu Chatterjee <sanchat@cal2.vsnl.net.in>

Background Information Relating to the Mystery Fever in North Bengal
--------------------------------------------------------------------
One of the differentials being considered is _Legionella_ infection. But, I
would think that it's too early to hazard a guess. Initial samples sent to
Calcutta were not stored under optimum conditions. It seems though that they
have now identified the index case. What seems most interesting is the
cluster of cases in one particular nursing home in the city, which has since
been closed. Nursing home, in our context, usually means a small private
hospital. Given the choice, people prefer getting treatment through such an
individual private health care option.
The death toll by Sat 24 Feb 2001 has reached 24. One death at the local
hospital due to "pneumonia" was 'mistakenly' included in the count, as per
the official report. The local authorities have decided to close schools for
4 days in order to disinfect the premises. In total, 37 people are
undergoing treatment at the local Medical College Hospital. Some cases
(fever, headache and semiconscious state) have been reported from adjoining
districts which are yet to be confirmed. Interestingly, the city (Siliguri)
is situated on the foothills of the Himalayas, in the northern part of West
Bengal state and is the most important commercial centre of that region --
many people (and students) from Sikkim, Bhutan , the North-Eastern Indian
states, adjoining part of Eastern Nepal and the hills come to this town to
trade or work or study.
--
Dr. Santanu Chatterjee
Consultant Physician - Travel & Tropical Medicine
11 Rupchand Mukherjee Lane
Calcutta - 700 025
India
<sanchat@cal2.vsnl.net.in>
[Dr. Chatterjee's comments help to put the situation in context. The press
report suggests that there may have been excessive delay in the referral of
diagnostic samples to central laboratories. It may be another week before
there is an identification of the causative agent. - Mod.CP
